# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version is
#   often managed by the user. If you are developing a terminal application or a data science
#   project, you might want to include them.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, if you'd like to ignore it, uncomment the following line:
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include poetry.lock in version control.
#   Poetry's own documentation suggests this: https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to include pdm.lock in version control.
